alerts.title: Wind Advisory
alerts.description:
...GUSTY NORTHERLY WINDS THROUGH TUESDAY EVENING...
...GUSTY SANTA ANA WINDS LATER TUESDAY NIGHT INTO THURSDAY...
.A TIGHTENING NORTHERLY SURFACE PRESSURE GRADIENT WILL BRING
INCREASING NORTHERLY WINDS TO PORTIONS OF SOUTHWEST CALIFORNIA
THROUGH TUESDAY EVENING...WITH THE STRONGEST WINDS EXPECTED
ACROSS THE INTERSTATE 5 CORRIDOR AND SANTA YNEZ MOUNTAINS. WINDS
WILL SHIFT TO THE NORTHEAST LATER TUESDAY NIGHT...WITH GUSTY
SANTA ANA WINDS EXPECTED TO CONTINUE ACROSS WIND PRONE AREAS OF
LOS ANGELES AND VENTURA COUNTIES THROUGH THURSDAY. THE GUSTY
NORTH TO NORTHEAST WINDS COMBINED WITH SIGNIFICANT WARMING AND
DRYING WILL BRING EXTREME FIRE DANGER TO PORTIONS OF SOUTHWEST
CALIFORNIA. PLEASE REFER TO THE LATEST RED FLAG WARNING PRODUCT
FOR FIRE WEATHER DETAILS.
...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM TUESDAY TO NOON PDT
THURSDAY...
* WINDS AND TIMING...AREAS OF NORTH WINDS INCREASING TO 15 TO 30
MPH WITH GUSTS TO 45 MPH BY EVENING...BECOMING NORTHEAST 20 TO
35 MPH WITH GUSTS 45 TO 55 MPH LATER TUESDAY NIGHT THROUGH
THURSDAY MORNING.
* IMPACTS...GUSTY WINDS WILL MAKE DRIVING DIFFICULT...ESPECIALLY
FOR DRIVERS OF HIGH PROFILE VEHICLES. THE GUSTY WINDS COULD
ALSO BRING DOWNED TREES AND POWER LINES AS WELL AS POWER
OUTAGES.

alerts.title: Beach Hazards Statement
alerts.description:
...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT REMAINS IN EFFECT THROUGH TUESDAY
AFTERNOON...
* HAZARDS...SURF WILL CONTINUE 4 TO 6 FEET WITH LOCAL SETS TO 7
FEET ALONG EXPOSED WEST FACING BEACHES.
* TIDES...HIGH TIDE AROUND 6.5 FEET WILL OCCUR BETWEEN 10 AND 11
AM PDT TUESDAY.
* IMPACTS...LARGE WAVES AND STRONG RIP CURRENTS WILL INCREASE
THE RISK OF OCEAN DROWNING. SNEAKER WAVES CAN SUDDENLY WASH
PEOPLE OFF OF BEACHES AND ROCK JETTIES INTO THE OCEAN. MORNING
HIGH TIDES WILL INCREASE WAVE RUNUP AND COASTAL EROSION.

alerts.title: Red Flag Warning
alerts.description:
...CRITICAL FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS TO DEVELOP FOR PORTIONS OF
SOUTHWEST CALIFORNIA FROM LATE TUESDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH THURSDAY
EVENING DUE TO GUSTY NORTH TO NORTHEAST WINDS AND VERY LOW
HUMIDITIES...
.A PROLONGED PERIOD OF CRITICAL FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS WILL
IMPACT PORTIONS OF SOUTHWEST CALIFORNIA FROM LATE TUESDAY
AFTERNOON THROUGH THURSDAY EVENING. INITIALLY...GUSTY NORTHERLY
WINDS AND DRYING CONDITIONS WILL AFFECT THE MOUNTAINS INCLUDING
THE SANTA MONICAS...THE SANTA BARBARA SOUTH COAST...AND PORTIONS
OF THE VALLEYS TUESDAY AFTERNOON INTO TUESDAY EVENING. WINDS ARE
EXPECTED TO SHIFT TO THE NORTHEAST LATER TUESDAY NIGHT AND REMAIN
GUSTY THROUGH THURSDAY...WITH CRITICAL FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS TO
DEVELOP ACROSS MUCH OF LOS ANGELES AND VENTURA COUNTIES. DURING
THIS TIME...GUSTY SANTA ANA WINDS WILL BRING SIGNIFICANT WARMING
AND DRYING...WITH WIDESPREAD SINGLE DIGIT HUMIDITIES AND VERY POOR
HUMIDITY RECOVERIES AT NIGHT. ANY FIRE IGNITIONS WILL HAVE THE
POTENTIAL FOR VERY RAPID FIRE SPREAD AND EXTREME FIRE BEHAVIOR DUE
TO THE COMBINATION OF CRITICAL FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS AND VERY
DRY FUELS.
...RED FLAG WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM WEDNESDAY TO 8 PM PDT
THURSDAY FOR GUSTY NORTHEAST WINDS AND VERY LOW RELATIVE HUMIDITY
FOR THE VENTURA COUNTY COAST AND LOS ANGELES COAST FROM MALIBU TO
HOLLYWOOD HILLS...
THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE IN LOS ANGELES/OXNARD HAS ISSUED A
RED FLAG WARNING FOR GUSTY NORTHEAST WINDS AND VERY LOW RELATIVE
HUMIDITY...WHICH IS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM WEDNESDAY TO 8 PM PDT
THURSDAY. THE FIRE WEATHER WATCH IS NO LONGER IN EFFECT.
* WINDS...AREAS OF NORTHEAST WINDS WILL INCREASE TO 15 TO 30 MPH
WITH GUSTS 35 TO 45 MPH AT TIMES ACROSS THE VENTURA COUNTY
COASTAL PLAIN AND MALIBU TO HOLLYWOOD HILLS BETWEEN WEDNESDAY
MORNING AND THURSDAY EVENING.
* RELATIVE HUMIDITY...WIDESPREAD AND LONG DURATION OF HUMIDITIES
BETWEEN 3 AND 15 PERCENT. VERY POOR HUMIDITY RECOVERIES AT
NIGHT.
* TEMPERATURES...DAYTIME HIGH TEMPERATURES WILL BE IN THE UPPER
80S TO MID 90S ON WEDNESDAY...THEN 90S TO AROUND 100 ON
THURSDAY.
* IMPACTS...THE COMBINATION OF GUSTY NORTHEAST WINDS...VERY LOW
HUMIDITY...AND WARM TEMPERATURES WILL CREATE CRITICAL FIRE
WEATHER CONDITIONS ACROSS THE WARNED AREA. THIS IN COMBINATION
WITH THE VERY DRY FUELS COULD CAUSE VERY RAPID FIRE SPREAD ALONG
WITH EXTREME FIRE DANGER AND FIRE BEHAVIOR.
